.TH PORTPING 1 "2026-05-14" "portping 2.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
portping \- TCP/UDP port connectivity checker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B portping
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIhost\fR \fIport\fR
.br
.B portping
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIhost\fR:\fIport\fR
.br
.B portping
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIhost\fR \fIport1,port2,...\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B portping
is a TCP port connectivity checker similar to
.BR ping (8),
but instead of sending ICMP echo requests, it attempts TCP connections
to a specified port. It measures connection time, detects port state
(open/refused/timeout), and provides detailed statistics.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c \fIcount\fR
Number of probes to send (default: infinite).
.TP
.B \-t \fIms\fR
Timeout per probe in milliseconds (default: 2000).
.TP
.B \-i \fIms\fR
Interval between probes in milliseconds (default: 1000).
.TP
.B \-w \fIsec\fR
Total deadline in seconds. Stop after this time regardless of count.
.TP
.B \-4
Force IPv4 resolution.
.TP
.B \-6
Force IPv6 resolution.
.TP
.B \-u
Use UDP instead of TCP.
.TP
.B \-S \fIaddr\fR
Bind to a specific source address.
.TP
.B \-I \fIiface\fR
Bind to a specific network interface (Linux only).
.TP
.B \-T
Show timestamp on each probe line.
.TP
.B \-q
Quiet mode. Only show summary.
.TP
.B \-b
Grab service banner after successful connection.
.TP
.B \-H \fIpath\fR
HTTP health check. Send GET request to path after connecting.
.TP
.B \-A
Alert (terminal bell) on state changes.
.TP
.B \-\-flood
Rapid-fire mode with no delay between probes.
.TP
.B \-\-csv
Output probe results in CSV format.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output summary statistics as JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-parallel \fIN\fR
Scan up to N ports simultaneously.
.TP
.B \-\-top\-ports \fIN\fR
Scan the top N most common ports (20, 50, or 100).
.TP
.B \-\-max\-rtt \fIms\fR
Exit with code 3 if average RTT exceeds threshold.
.TP
.B \-\-max\-jitter \fIms\fR
Exit with code 2 if jitter exceeds threshold.
.TP
.B \-\-max\-loss \fIpct\fR
Exit with code 4 if loss percentage exceeds threshold.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
At least one probe succeeded (or port closed with \-\-expect\-closed).
.TP
.B 1
All probes failed.
.TP
.B 2
Jitter threshold exceeded.
.TP
.B 3
RTT threshold exceeded.
.TP
.B 4
Loss threshold exceeded.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Basic connectivity check
portping example.com 443

# Scan common ports in parallel
portping --top-ports 20 --parallel 20 server.com

# HTTP health check with SLA monitoring
portping -H /health --max-rtt 200 -c 100 api.example.com 8080

# Wait for service to be ready
portping --until-open -i 500 db-server 5432
.fi
